Global Grid-tied PV Inverter Market Insights
Grid-tied PV Inverter Market size was valued at USD 8.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 14.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Grid-tied PV Inverter Market Overview
The global Grid-tied PV Inverter market is valued at approximately USD 10.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 7.2% during the forecast period from 2025 to 2030. This growth is driven by the increasing adoption of renewable energy sources, particularly solar power, across both residential and commercial sectors. Grid-tied PV inverters are essential for converting DC power from solar panels into AC power, facilitating integration with the power grid. As governments and businesses focus on reducing carbon emissions, the demand for energy-efficient solar technologies continues to rise globally.

